  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients who are hospitalized in intensive care unit (ICU) require basic nursing care to
      improve patient hygiene, to promote comfort, to prevent pressure ulcer, and foot or hand's
      retractations.

      Those nursing cares require mobilization very frequently which expose critically ill patients
      to occurrence of serious adverse events (SAE) such as i) hemodynamic, neurologic, and
      respiratory variations ii) unplanned dislodgement (lines, drains, catheters, endotracheal
      tube..)

      Few study have evaluated relation between SAE occurence and several patient's, service's,
      health-care provider's caracteristics. We plan to analyse those factors to find some ways to
      prevent SAE occurence during nursing and hygiene cares.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
